      "All clear announced after gas levels returned to zero",
      "Operations continued after incident discussion"
    ],
    "summary": "On 15 November 2024 at 0837 hours, a gas release occurred in the shaker house onboard the Valaris DS-16 drillship during well abandonment operations at Garden Banks 668. While attempting to bullhead well SS011, a hydrate plug formed in the production tubing. The crew displaced the landing string and kill line with nitrogen to dissipate the hydrate, then attempted to displace back to 12.2 ppg CaBr2. During this displacement, the liquid leg of the mud gas separator was compromised, allowing hydrocarbon gas to bypass the separator and enter the shaker house, triggering a hydrocarbon alarm and requiring full crew muster. Gas levels returned to zero and operations resumed without further issues.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Conduct safety meetings with all four crews expressing the importance of circulating fluids/gases from well and how it could impact the mud gas separator liquid leg",
      "Recognize that liquid leg can be impacted differently with mud, brine, and nitrogen in the circulating system"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "hydrate plug",
      "liquid leg compromised",
      "mud gas separator",
      "hydrocarbon alarm",
      "nitrogen displacement",
      "bullhead operation",
      "shaker house"
    ]
  },
